messages.message: There's currently an npm service outage (https://status.npmjs.org/) that is causing jenkins builds to fail because it's unable to pull packages from our private npm registry. They fail very early without actually doing any checks, so we probably shouldn't merge any PRs until it's back up. I'll message out to this channel when I see that it is back up so that we can rerun our jenkins jobs and get those PRs in.
This is affecting me more negatively than the facebook outage tbh :rolling_on_the_floor_laughing:
They've identified the fix so hopefully not too much longer!!
